<observation-set xmlns="http://vortex.cis.vtc.edu/xml/AOML_0.0"
  xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
  xsi:schemaLocation="http://vortex.cis.vtc.edu/xml/AOML_0.0 ../AOML/AOML.xsd">

  <location>
    <value>
      <lat-long-alt>+43.00-072.50+300</lat-long-alt>
    </value>
    <notes>
      <xhtml:p>Central Vermont, USA</xhtml:p>
    </notes>
  </location>
  <observer>Peter C. Chapin</observer>
  <notes>
    <xhtml:p>The temperature and humidity measurements shown here were all made with a La Crosse
      WS-7078SUF weather station.</xhtml:p>
  </notes>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-01T20:55:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">0.0</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">92</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>It's been freezing raining most of the day. This evening it is totally cloudy
            with extensive ground fog.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The sky is unobservable.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>0</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-02T21:10:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-4.6</value>
        </temperature>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>It's perfectly clear with no clounds.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The moon is nearly full, but conditions are good. The air is clear and many
          stars are visible.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>3</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-06T22:40:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">6.7</value>
        </temperature>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Partly cloudy and unseasonably warm.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>A large moon is well above the eastern horizon. The sky is about 80% covered
          with clouds. The clarity is good in the clear patches, however. The clouds are thick
          enough to render the moon as unobservable when it is covered (which is most of the
          time).</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>1</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-08T22:00:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">1.4</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">75</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Partly cloudy.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The sky is about 50% covered with clouds. However, many stars are visible in
          the clear sections. The moon has not yet risen so the sky is nicely dark.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>3</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-09T20:40:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-0.7</value>
        </temperature>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Mostly cloudy. A thin layer of fresh snow on the ground.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Only the brightest stars are visible through the clouds.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>1</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-14T21:50:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-3.2</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">86</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Mostly cloudy. A thin layer of fresh snow on the ground.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Only the brightest stars are visible through the clouds.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>1</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-01-17T06:00:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-20.6</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">75</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Perfectly clear and quite cold.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>Conditions are excellent this morning. No clouds are in the sky and the air
          clarity is good. At this time there is some brightening in the east, but most of the
          sky is still dark. Deep sky objects observable even in Lyr (which has only recently
          risen).</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>4</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LDT" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-08-14T21:40:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">14.0</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">77</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Fine clouds or hazy uniformly covering the sky.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>All bright stars and many fainter stars are visible. However, haze or clouds
          obscure the faintest stars, making the night significantly less than ideal.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>3</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-12-21T18:05:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">-5.8</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">83</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Mostly clear with some clouds here and there. Sky appears to be a bit
          hazy.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The bright moon is lighting up the sky and preventing many stars from being
          visible. The clouds and thin hazy is also lite by the moon and that aggravates the
          situation. Despite that the brighter stars are visible. For example, bright double
          stars could be observed over most of the sky.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>2</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

  <observation>
    <localdatetime type="LST" resolution="PT10M">
      <ISO>2007-12-29T20:50:00</ISO>
    </localdatetime>
    <skyconditions>
      <weather>
        <temperature>
          <value units="C">1.3</value>
        </temperature>
        <humidity>
          <value units="%">76</value>
        </humidity>
        <notes>
          <xhtml:p>Completely cloudy.</xhtml:p>
        </notes>
      </weather>
      <notes>
        <xhtml:p>The sky is unobservable.</xhtml:p>
      </notes>
      <rating>0</rating>
    </skyconditions>
  </observation>

</observation-set>
